File: Emergency paramedics wearing a full COVID-19 coronavirus personal protective equipment (PPE) transfer an empty gurney to an ambulance at the Greenacres Hospital in Port Elizabeth. Marco Longari / AFP JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded it's worst day for COVID-19 infections yet. In the last twenty four hours, 21,980 new infections have been added. It's the third day in a row that more than 20,000 cases have been confirmed. READ: New coronavirus variant 'not out of control': WHO This takes the total number of cases to over 1,1 million. Six-hundred and sixteen new deaths have been reported, taking the death toll to 32,425 Over 900,000 people have already recovered from the virus. More than 7 million tests have been conducted, over 76,000 of those since the last report.